In the present work, we have investigated laminar to turbulent transition of Kolmogorov ï¬‚ow in strongly coupled Yukawa liquid using â€œï¬rst principleâ€ based molecular
FIG. 12. Decay rate vs a Â¼ U0=vth plot for the number of perturbation mode m Â¼ 2, coupling parameter C0 Â¼ 50, screening parameter j Â¼ 0:5; equilibrium spatial period number n0 Â¼ 3.

dynamics simulation. Parametric study for range of Reynolds number R has been performed and reveals that the Yukawa liquid in neutral stable state for R < Rc and unstable for R > Rc, where Rc is a transition point from where laminar to turbulent transition occurs. The nature of the growth of perturbed mode against Reynolds number exhibits transcritical like bifurcation. We have presented the effect of molecular shear heating on the stability of shear ï¬‚ow in Yukawa liquid. In the early phase, we ï¬nd that the coupling parameter decays exponentially. At the late times, coherent vortices are destroyed because of molecular shear heating. The description of viscous heating is characterized by space dependent temperature proï¬le at a given coupling parameter (C0 Â¼ 50) of x at y Â¼ 0 for different times. These space dependent temperature proï¬les reveal the rise in temperature at shear location. It is also seen that the decay-rate of C with time depends upon the ratio of equilibrium shear velocity to thermal velocity. The inï¬‚uence of suppressed molecular shear heating on shear ï¬‚ow to represent the ï¬‚uid properties without heat dissipation in strongly coupled dusty plasma will be presented in future communication.
